  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want my wallet balance to update immediately when I receive ETH.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Currently wallet balance updates can (or will be able to soon) be updated when you \"pull down the the screen\" to refresh. It might be desirable to automatically update wallet balance when you send/receive ETH. Receiving ETH can happen outside of app, so there are a few approaches we can take here:\r\n\r\n(1) Polling for wallet balance every 10s (like we do with sync)\r\n(2) Listen for incoming transactions and filter out relevant events for account, then trigger update\r\n(3) Leave it as it is and require user to refresh wallet manually\r\n(4) Your idea here",
